The paper proposes a method to identify influential nodes in complex networks and uses the Susceptible-Infected (SI) model to simulate the spreading process. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper focuses on the local dimension of center nodes, which could fall under the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The use of real-world networks and centrality measures also suggests the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper uses fuzzy set theory, which could fall under the sub-category of Soft Computing (cs.SC).
